reviews.review: An adequate ending to an ill conceived trilogy.

For people who like having flashy things being flashed at them, they will love the movie. For those who look for substance based on actual character background and philosophy, you will hate the movie. 
Where do I start? 
1. Being a skywalker meant nothing. 
2. Being trained meant nothing. 
3. How emperor survive fall wasn't addressed.
4. Why do you need a star killer when the emperor can just force lightning the whole planet?

Rey was depicted as the strongest ever with no training or knowledge of anything other than how to pick up trash for money. 

I don't have words to describe the disappointment I feel for this movie.

Typical Disney esk style of SW. many parts seemed very easy to predict what was going to happen. it almost felt like the story was rushed and overall changing the original canon stories to match what disney is wanting to go with the saga is disappointing...unless your disney fan.

It was the perfect ending to the story. Lots of action and answers to many of the questions we all wondered about. I was very satisfied with this movie. As a Star Wars fan from the first movie on I shed a few tears.
I'm the biggest Star Wars fan that I know and I hated everything about it. Massive disappointment!
An awesome fun, funny, exhilarating end to the most epic of sagas!
I loved it!!  In my opinion this is what a Star Wars movie is supposed to be.  More true to episodes 4-6.
It was more like the original Star wars than 1,2 and 3. Like the way the original characters were blended in. Was a shock to find out who Ray's parents were. Definetly worth seeing!!!

Rey & Kylo Ren shine in this last installment of the Star Wars saga.  The first half is very fast paced with all characters hitting the ground running.  Once the movie slows down to focus on story and character development it improves.  There's a lot for the fans here, some would argue too much is crammed into one movie (I agree with this camp).  Looking back, the trilogy would have been better served by one director all the way through.  JJ Abrams did what he could to salvage this movie, but there are some obvious choices made in story, pacing and character dialogue (or lack of) that suffer on the final editing floor. Still, the visuals and score are stunning and make up for some of the movie's core flaws.
